narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I think that more structure could help--granted, it was one of the strengths of the course, that it was so freeform and topics that could never be reached in other classes were talked about, but I wish we would focus more on specific techniques at times.

Class great in its flexibility; there is a lot of writing but you can write about anything you want; also somewhat lenient with deadlines; awesome assigned reading; Zarin incredibly insightful (especially great when get to meet with her individually)

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, those who are interested in writing. It's a light-workload class that gets to the meat-and-potatoes of essay writing.

If you want to get better at writing personal essays take the course; you're bound to get better through the practice of writing and the assigned reading; like a lot of creative writing classes quality deviates somewhat based on composition of class itself; discussions were sometimes dull since students didn't do the reading or clearly wrote essays at last minute; you get out what you put in
